{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889959444,"sessionID":"ses_284b6dcd9ffeKUGA3ZF6QyYYPP","part":{"id":"prt_d7b4a49f1001KTLbkfy6mcL85N","messageID":"msg_d7b4a4141001snppMek7Jbjd2G","sessionID":"ses_284b6dcd9ffeKUGA3ZF6QyYYPP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e690d479b700405e8f18d1cb81b50d70","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-036 Dify Plugin Integration\n2: \n3: ## AR Metadata\n4: - **AR ID**: AR-036\n5: - **Title**: Dify 插件集成\n6: - **Module**: integrations\n7: - **Language**: Python\n8: - **Size**: M\n9: - **Status**: Implementation Required\n10: \n11: ## Purpose\n12: \n13: Implementation deltas for adding Dify plugin integration to the AgentCube project, including the Python SDK client library and PCAP analyzer example application.\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Create Dify plugin package structure\n18: \n19: The system SHALL create a complete Dify plugin package under `integrations/dify-plugin/` with all required manifest files, provider descriptors, tool definitions, and Python implementations.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Plugin directory layout exists\n22: \n23: - **GIVEN** a new `integrations/dify-plugin/` directory\n24: - **WHEN** the package structure is created\n25: - **THEN** the directory SHALL contain `main.py`, `manifest.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.py`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`, `requirements.txt`, `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, and `.difyignore`\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ### Requirement: Implement plugin manifest\n30: \n31: The system SHALL implement `manifest.yaml` with all required fields including version, type, author, name, multilingual labels/descriptions, icons, resource permissions, tool provider references, and runner metadata.\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: Manifest contains all required fields\n34: \n35: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml`\n36: - **WHEN** the file is parsed by Dify toolchain\n37: - **THEN** the manifest SHALL include `version: 0.0.2`, `type: plugin`, `author: volcano-sh`, `name: agentcube`, `label` with multilingual map for `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR`, `description` with multilingual strings, `icon: icon.png`, `icon_dark: icon-dark.png`, `resource` subtree with `memory` and `permission` flags, `plugins.tools: [provider/agentcube.yaml]`, and `meta` with `version`, `arch` (amd64, arm64), `runner` (language: python, version: \"3.12\", entrypoint: main), and `minimum_dify_version: null`\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ### Requirement: Implement provider descriptor\n42: \n43: The system SHALL implement `provider/agentcube.yaml` with identity fields and tool list pointing to the code interpreter tool.\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Provider descriptor structure\n46: \n47: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml`\n48: - **WHEN** the provider is loaded by Dify\n49: - **THEN** the file SHALL contain `identity` with `author`, `name`, multilingual `label`, multilingual `description`, `icon`, a `tools` list containing `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, and `extra.python.source: provider/agentcube.py`\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Implement tool schema\n54: \n55: The system SHALL implement `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` with the complete parameter schema for the code interpreter integration.\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Tool parameter schema\n58: \n59: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n60: - **WHEN** the tool is configured in Dify\n61: - **THEN** the schema SHALL define `identity` with `name: agentcube-code-interpreter`, `author: agentcube`, multilingual `label` and `description`, and `parameters` array with `router_url` (string, required, form), `workload_manager_url` (string, required, form), `language` (select, options: python, javascript, typescript, llm), `code` (string, llm), `command` (string, llm), `session_id` (string, llm), `session_reuse` (boolean, llm), and `code_interpreter_id` (string, llm), each with `label`, `human_description`, `llm_description`, and `form` fields\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ### Requirement: Implement plugin main entry\n66: \n67: The system SHALL implement `main.py` that runs the Dify plugin framework with a 120-second request timeout.\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Plugin process entrypoint\n70: \n71: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py`\n72: - **WHEN** Dify starts the plugin\n73: - **THEN** the file SHALL execute `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Implement provider class\n78: \n79: The system SHALL implement `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` class that extends `ToolProvider` with credential validation.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Provider class structure\n82: \n83: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py`\n84: - **WHEN** the provider class is instantiated\n85: - **THEN** it SHALL define `class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider)` with `_validate_credentials` method that may raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError`\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ### Requirement: Implement tool class\n90: \n91: The system SHALL implement `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` class that extends `Tool` and delegates to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`.\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Tool class invocation\n94: \n95: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n96: - **WHEN** Dify invokes the tool\n97: - **THEN** the class SHALL define `class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool)` with `_invoke` method that calls `execute(**tool_parameters)` and yields `create_json_message(result)`, and an `execute` method accepting `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, `language` (default \"python\"), `code_interpreter_id`, `session_id`, `code`, `command`, `session_reuse`, and delegating to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ### Requirement: Create plugin dependencies\n102: \n103: The system SHALL create `requirements.txt` with pinned versions of `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk`.\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Dependency specification\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n108: - **WHEN** dependencies are installed\n109: - **THEN** the file SHALL contain `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ### Requirement: Create Python SDK package\n114: \n115: The system SHALL create the complete `agentcube-sdk` Python package under `sdk-python/` with all client classes and utilities.\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: SDK package layout\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** `sdk-python/` directory\n120: - **WHEN** the SDK is structured\n121: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `pyproject.toml`, `agentcube/__init__.py`, `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`, `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`, `agentcube/exceptions.py`, `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`, `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`, `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`, `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`, `agentcube/utils/http.py`, `agentcube/utils/utils.py`, `agentcube/utils/log.py`, and `agentcube/utils/__init__.py`\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: Implement CodeInterpreterClient\n126: \n127: The system SHALL implement `CodeInterpreterClient` with session management, file operations, code execution, and command execution.\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Client initialization\n130: \n131: - **GIVEN** `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n132: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated\n133: - **THEN** it SHALL accept `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url` (or from `ROUTER_URL` env), `auth_token`, `verbose`, and `session_id`, initialize `ControlPlaneClient` and `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and raise `ValueError` if `router_url` is not provided\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n136: \n137: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` instance used as context manager\n138: - **WHEN** the context exits\n139: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()` which closes the data plane session, deletes the control plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Command execution with non-zero exit\n142: \n143: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called\n144: - **WHEN** the remote command returns `exit_code != 0`\n145: - **THEN** the method SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Python code execution\n148: \n149: - **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with `language` as `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n150: - **WHEN** the code is executed\n151: - **THEN** the method SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### Requirement: Implement AgentRuntimeClient\n156: \n157: The system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeClient` with session bootstrap, invocation, and lifecycle management.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Client initialization and session bootstrap\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n162: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated without `session_id`\n163: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`, raising `ValueError` if the header is missing\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Invoke without session\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeClient` instance with falsy `session_id`\n168: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n169: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ### Requirement: Implement ControlPlaneClient\n174: \n175: The system SHALL implement `ControlPlaneClient` with session creation and deletion via the Workload Manager API.\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Create session\n178: \n179: - **GIVEN** a `ControlPlaneClient` instance\n180: - **WHEN** `create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)` is called\n181: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body containing `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, and `metadata`, and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: Delete session with 404\n184: \n185: - **GIVEN** a `ControlPlaneClient` instance\n186: - **WHEN** `delete_session(session_id)` is called and server returns 404\n187: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n188: \n189: ---\n190: \n191: ### Requirement: Implement CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n192: \n193: The system SHALL implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with file operations, command execution, and code execution via the Router API.\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Execute command with timeout buffer\n196: \n197: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` instance\n198: - **WHEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=<value>)` posts to `api/execute`\n199: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON with `command` array and `timeout` string, and the read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: File write operation\n202: \n203: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` instance\n204: - **WHEN** `write_file(content, remote_path)` is called\n205: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64-encoded `content`, `path`, and `mode: \"0644\"`\n206: \n207: ---\n208: \n209: ### Requirement: Implement AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n210: \n211: The system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with session bootstrap and invocation via the Router API.\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Invoke with timeout tuple\n214: \n215: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` instance\n216: - **WHEN** `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout=None)` is called\n217: - **THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to 120\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ### Requirement: Implement exception hierarchy\n222: \n223: The system SHALL define the complete exception hierarchy in `agentcube/exceptions.py`.\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Exception classes defined\n226: \n227: - **GIVEN** `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n228: - **WHEN** exceptions are imported\n229: - **THEN** it SHALL define `AgentCubeError` (base), `CommandExecutionError` (with `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command`), `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError`\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: ### Requirement: Implement utility modules\n234: \n235: The system SHALL implement utility modules for HTTP session creation, token reading, and logging.\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: HTTP session with pooling\n238: \n239: - **GIVEN** `agentcube/utils/http.py`\n240: - **WHEN** `create_session` is called\n241: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` mounted for both `http://` and `https://` with `pool_connections` and `pool_maxsize` defaulting to 10\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: Token from file\n244: \n245: - **GIVEN** `agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n246: - **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(file_path)` is called\n247: - **THEN** it SHALL return file contents stripped, or empty string on `FileNotFoundError`\n248: \n249: ---\n250: \n251: ### Requirement: Configure SDK package metadata\n252: \n253: The system SHALL configure `pyproject.toml` with package metadata, dependencies, and build configuration.\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: Package configuration\n256: \n257: - **GIVEN** `sdk-python/pyproject.toml`\n258: - **WHEN** the package is built\n259: - **THEN** it SHALL declare package name `agentcube-sdk`, `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`, dependencies including `requests`, `PyJWT>=2.0.0`, and `cryptography`, build backend `setuptools.build_meta`, and package discovery for `agentcube*` modules\n260: \n261: ---\n262: \n263: ### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer application\n264: \n265: The system SHALL create a FastAPI application under `example/pcap-analyzer/` that uses AgentCube code interpreters for PCAP analysis.\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Application structure\n268: \n269: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/` directory\n270: - **WHEN** the example application is structured\n271: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `pcap_analyzer.py`, `requirements.txt`, `Dockerfile`, `deployment.yaml`, and `README.md`\n272: \n273: ---\n274: \n275: ### Requirement: Implement PCAP analyzer core classes\n276: \n277: The system SHALL implement `SandboxRunner`, agent builders, and analysis orchestration functions in `pcap_analyzer.py`.\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: SandboxRunner operations\n280: \n281: - **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner` instance\n282: - **WHEN** methods are called\n283: - **THEN** it SHALL provide `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`, `upload_bytes(data, remote_path)`, `run(command)`, and `stop()` methods\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: Agent builders\n286: \n287: - **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` imports\n288: - **WHEN** agent builders are called\n289: - **THEN** it SHALL provide `build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt)`, `invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text)`, `build_planner_agent(llm)`, and `build_reporter_agent(llm)` functions\n290: \n291: #### Scenario: Analysis orchestration\n292: \n293: - **GIVEN** analysis functions\n294: - **WHEN** PCAP analysis is performed\n295: - **THEN** it SHALL provide `_plan_script`, `_repair_script`, `_execute_once_in_runner`, `_analyze_with_retries`, and `_report` functions\n296: \n297: ---\n298: \n299: ### Requirement: Implement PCAP analyzer endpoints\n300: \n301: The system SHALL implement FastAPI endpoints for startup validation and PCAP analysis.\n302: \n303: #### Scenario: Startup validation\n304: \n305: - **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` startup event\n306: - **WHEN** the application starts\n307: - **THEN** it SHALL fail if `OPENAI_API_KEY` (or configured API key) is not available, and build `ChatOpenAI`, `PLANNER`, and `REPORTER` agents\n308: \n309: #### Scenario: Analyze endpoint\n310: \n311: - **GIVEN** `POST /analyze` endpoint\n312: - **WHEN** called with either `pcap_file: UploadFile` or `pcap_path: str` form field\n313: - **THEN** it SHALL return `AnalyzeResponse` with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ### Requirement: Configure PCAP analyzer environment\n318: \n319: The system SHALL configure environment variable bindings for OpenAI-compatible API, model selection, and AgentCube sandbox parameters.\n320: \n321: #### Scenario: Environment configuration\n322: \n323: - **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` configuration\n324: - **WHEN** the service starts\n325: - **THEN** it SHALL read `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `OPENAI_API_BASE` (default `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`), `OPENAI_MODEL` (default `Qwen/QwQ-32B`), `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` (default `my-interpreter`), `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` (default `default`), and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` (default `5`)\n326: \n327: ---\n328: \n329: ### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer dependencies\n330: \n331: The system SHALL create `requirements.txt` with all required Python dependencies.\n332: \n333: #### Scenario: Dependency list\n334: \n335: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`\n336: - **WHEN** dependencies are installed\n337: - **THEN** it SHALL include `fastapi==0.120.0`, `uvicorn==0.38.0`, and the full LangChain/LangGraph stack with pinned versions\n338: \n339: ---\n340: \n341: ### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer Dockerfile\n342: \n343: The system SHALL create a Dockerfile that builds the PCAP analyzer image with `uv` and vendors the agentcube SDK.\n344: \n345: #### Scenario: Image build\n346: \n347: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile`\n348: - **WHEN** the image is built\n349: - **THEN** it SHALL use base `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`, run `uv venv`, install dependencies with `uv pip install`, copy `sdk-python/agentcube` to `./agentcube/`, copy `pcap_analyzer.py` to root, set `PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"`, expose port 8000, and set `CMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer Kubernetes deployment\n354: \n355: The system SHALL create `deployment.yaml` with Deployment manifest for the analyzer.\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Deployment manifest\n358: \n359: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml`\n360: - **WHEN** applied to cluster\n361: - **THEN** it SHALL create `Deployment` `pcap-analyzer` in `namespace: default`, run container `pcap-analyzer` with image `pcap-analyzer:latest`, listen on TCP 8000, set resource requests `cpu: 200m` and `memory: 100Mi` with limits `cpu: 1` and `memory: 1Gi`, mount `OPENAI_API_KEY` from Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets`, and set environment variables for all API and sandbox parameters\n362: \n363: ---\n364: \n365: ### Requirement: Create plugin documentation\n366: \n367: The system SHALL create `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, and `.difyignore` for the Dify plugin.\n368: \n369: #### Scenario: Documentation files exist\n370: \n371: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/` directory\n372: - **WHEN** documentation is complete\n373: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `GUIDE.md` with usage instructions, `README.md` with project overview, `PRIVACY.md` with privacy policy, and `.difyignore` with packaging exclusions\n374: \n375: ---\n376: \n377: ### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer README\n378: \n379: The system SHALL create `README.md` for the PCAP analyzer example.\n380: \n381: #### Scenario: Example documentation exists\n382: \n383: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/` directory\n384: - **WHEN** documentation is complete\n385: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `README.md` with setup, usage, and deployment instructions\n386: \n387: ---\n388: \n389: ### Requirement: Ensure session header naming\n390: \n391: The system SHALL ensure all SDK Router requests use the lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n392: \n393: #### Scenario: Session header consistency\n394: \n395: - **GIVEN** SDK data plane clients\n396: - **WHEN** making Router requests\n397: - **THEN** both `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL use header `x-agentcube-session-id` (with appropriate casing for the constant name)\n398: \n399: ---\n400: \n401: ### Requirement: Ensure timeout defaults\n402: \n403: The system SHALL ensure control-plane and data-plane clients default to 120-second read timeout and 5-second connect timeout.\n404: \n405: #### Scenario: Timeout defaults applied\n406: \n407: - **GIVEN** client initialization\n408: - **WHEN** no custom timeouts are provided\n409: - **THEN** `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL use `timeout=120` and `connect_timeout=5.0`\n410: \n411: ---\n412: \n413: ### Requirement: Handle router URL environment variable\n414: \n415: The system SHALL ensure `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` resolve `router_url` from argument or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable.\n416: \n417: #### Scenario: Router URL resolution\n418: \n419: - **GIVEN** client instantiation\n420: - **WHEN** `router_url` is not provided as argument\n421: - **THEN** both clients SHALL read from `ROUTER_URL` environment variable and raise `ValueError` if not set\n422: \n423: ---\n424: \n425: ### Requirement: Handle workload manager URL and auth token\n426: \n427: The system SHALL ensure `ControlPlaneClient` resolves `workload_manager_url` from argument or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env, and `auth_token` from argument or SA token file.\n428: \n429: #### Scenario: Workload Manager configuration\n430: \n431: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` instantiation\n432: - **WHEN** `workload_manager_url` is not provided\n433: - **THEN** it SHALL read from `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable\n434: \n435: #### Scenario: Auth token resolution\n436: \n437: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` instantiation without `auth_token`\n438: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n439: - **THEN** it SHALL read from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file` and set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header if token is non-empty\n440: \n441: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n442: \n443: 1. ✅ Dify plugin package structure created with all required files\n444: 2. ✅ Plugin manifest includes all required fields\n445: 3. ✅ Provider descriptor properly configured\n446: 4. ✅ Tool schema with complete parameter definitions\n447: 5. ✅ Plugin main entry point runs Dify framework\n448: 6. ✅ Provider class with credential validation\n449: 7. ✅ Tool class delegates to agentcube SDK\n450: 8. ✅ Plugin dependencies pinned correctly\n451: 9. ✅ Python SDK package structure complete\n452: 10. ✅ CodeInterpreterClient implements session management\n453: 11. ✅ AgentRuntimeClient implements session bootstrap and invocation\n454: 12. ✅ ControlPlaneClient implements session CRUD operations\n455: 13. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient implements file and command operations\n456: 14. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient implements invocation with session management\n457: 15. ✅ Exception hierarchy defined\n458: 16. ✅ Utility modules for HTTP, token, and logging\n459: 17. ✅ SDK package metadata configured\n460: 18. ✅ PCAP analyzer application structure\n461: 19. ✅ PCAP analyzer core classes and orchestration\n462: 20. ✅ PCAP analyzer FastAPI endpoints\n463: 21. ✅ PCAP analyzer environment configuration\n464: 22. ✅ PCAP analyzer dependencies specified\n465: 23. ✅ PCAP analyzer Dockerfile\n466: 24. ✅ PCAP analyzer Kubernetes deployment\n467: 25. ✅ Plugin documentation files\n468: 26. ✅ PCAP analyzer documentation\n469: 27. ✅ Session header naming consistent\n470: 28. ✅ Timeout defaults applied\n471: 29. ✅ Router URL environment variable handling\n472: 30. ✅ Workload manager URL and auth token handling\n473: \n474: ## Dependencies\n475: \n476: - `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`\n477: - `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n478: - `requests`\n479: - `PyJWT>=2.0.0`\n480: - `cryptography`\n481: - `fastapi==0.120.0`\n482: - `uvicorn==0.38.0`\n483: - LangChain/LangGraph stack\n484: - Python >=3.10\n485: \n486: ## References\n487: \n488: - Base Design: `integrations/design.md`\n489: - Base Specification: `integrations/spec.md`\n490: - Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n491: - Base Specification: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n492: - AR: AR-036 — Dify 插件集成\n\n(End of file - total 492 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-036 Dify Plugin Integration\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-036\n- **Title**: Dify 插件集成\n- **Module**: integrations\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplementation deltas for adding Dify plugin integration to the AgentCube project, including the Python SDK client library and PCAP analyzer example application.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Create Dify plugin package structure\n\nThe system SHALL create a complete Dify plugin package under `integrations/dify-plugin/` with all required manifest files, provider descriptors, tool definitions, and Python implementations.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775889959425,"end":1775889959441}}}}
